snippet: Osmo Vanska resigned on Tuesday as music director of the Minnesota Orchestra, a day after the orchestra announced that it had canceled two concerts at Carnegie Hall.
abstract: Conductor Osmo Vanska resigns from Minnesota Orchestra after it cancels two concerts he had planned for Carnegie Hall; orchestra's players have been locked out for a year over contract disputes.
lead_paragraph: Osmo Vanska resigned on Tuesday as music director of the Minnesota Orchestra, a day after the orchestra announced that it had canceled two concerts at Carnegie Hall.

headline.main: Vanska Quits Minnesota Orchestra as Labor Dispute Drags On
